wikipedia_page.main: James Spencer-Bell (18 April 1818 – 22 February 1872), known until 1866 as James Bell, was a British Liberal Party politician. He was a member of parliament (MP) for Guildford from 1852 until 1857.

response: *James Spencer-Bell (1818–1872), known until 1866 as James Bell, MP for Guildford
He had married in 1892 Juliet Spencer-Bell, daughter of MP James Spencer-Bell.
